-- U.K. Stocks Climb as Utilities Scottish & Southern, Severn Trent Advance
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-10-29T13:47:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/stocks-climb-as-utilities-scottish-southern-severn-trent-centrica-gain.html
U.K. stocks climbed, led by a rally
in utility shares.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index rose 0.3 percent to 5,694.78
at 2:44 p.m. in London.  Scottish & Southern Energy Plc, Centrica Plc and Severn
Trent Plc all rose more than 2 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
